msContents.summary: Homily by Origen written 200-254 in Alexandria, Aegyptus

objectDesc.p: Papyrus, 12.7x10.2 (?), 1 extant leaf(s), 1 column(s), 19 (?) line(s) per column, 23-25 characters per line, written in Greek.

history.provenance: Excavated 1905-1906 by Bernard Grenfell and Arthur Hunt, Egypt Exploration Society at Al Bahnasā, Miṣr from a garbage dump.
Donated to United Theological Seminary, O'Brien Library at Dayton, OH.

msIdentifier.msName: P. Oxy. 1601, United Theological Seminary, O'Brien Library, Dayton, OH.
